{"article_id":"28HeIQdY65cNHS80","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"An elite crew of firefighters","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"trained","depth":11},{"id":2,"text":"to battle the nation 's fiercest wildfires","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"was overtaken by an out-of-control blaze in Arizona ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"killing 19 members","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"as they tried to protect themselves from the flames under fire-resistant shields .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"It was the most firefighters","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"killed battling a wildfire in the U.S. in decades .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The lightning-sparked fire ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"which spread to at least 2,000 acres","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"( 800 hectares )","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"amid triple-digit temperatures ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"also destroyed 200 homes","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and sent hundreds fleeing from Yarnell , a town of about 700 residents about 85 miles","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"( 135 kilometers )","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"northwest of Phoenix .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"Residents huddled in shelters and bars ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"watching their homes burn on TV","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"as flames lit up the night sky in the forest above the town .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"The disaster Sunday afternoon all but wiped out the 20-member Hotshot fire crew","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"based in nearby Prescott ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"leaving the city 's fire department reeling .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"`` We grieve for the family .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"We grieve for the department .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"We grieve for the city , ''","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"Prescott Fire Chief Dan Fraijo said at a news conference Sunday evening .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"`` We 're devastated .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"We just lost 19 of the finest people","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"you 'll ever meet . ''","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"The National Fire Protection Association website lists the last wildland fire","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"to kill more firefighters","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"as the 1933 Griffith Park fire of Los Angeles ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"which killed 29 .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"The most firefighters","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"- 340 -","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"were killed in the 9/11 terrorist attacks in New York ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"according to the website .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Most people had evacuated from the town ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"and no injuries or other deaths were reported .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Hotshot crews go through specialized training","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"and are often deployed","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"soon after a fire breaks out .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Sometimes they hike for miles into the wilderness with chain saws and backpacks","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"filled with heavy gear","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"to build lines of protection between people and fires .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"They remove brush , trees and anything","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that might burn in the direction of homes and cities .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"This crew had worked other wildfires in recent weeks in New Mexico and Arizona .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"As a last-ditch effort at survival , Hotshot crew members are trained to dig into the ground","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and cover themselves with the tent-like shelter","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"made of fire-resistant material ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Fraijo said .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"The hope in that desperate situation is that the fire will burn over them","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"and they will survive .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"`` It 's an extreme measure","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that 's taken under the absolute worst conditions , ''","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Fraijo said .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Nineteen fire shelters were deployed ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and some of the firefighters were found inside them ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"while others were outside the shelters ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Mike Reichling , Arizona State Forestry Division spokesman , told the Arizona Republic .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Prescott ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"which is more than 30 miles","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"( 50 kilometers )","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"northeast of Yarnell ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"is home to one of 110 Hotshot crews in the United States ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"according to the U.S. Forest Service website .","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"The unit was established in 2002 ,","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"and the city also has 75 suppression team members .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"In 1994 , the Storm King Fire near Glenwood Springs , Colorado , killed 14 firefighters","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"who were overtaken by a sudden explosion of flames .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"President Barack Obama called the 19 firefighters heroes","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"and said in a statement","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"that the federal government was assisting state and local officials .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"`` This is as dark a day","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"as I can remember , ''","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Gov . Jan Brewer said in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"`` It may be days or longer","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"before an investigation reveals","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"how this tragedy occurred ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"but the essence","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"we already know in our hearts :","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"fighting fires is dangerous work . ''","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Brewer said","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"she would travel to the area on Monday .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"As the blaze spread ,","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"people started fleeing ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"including Chuck Overmyer and his wife , Ninabill .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"They were helping friends leave","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"when the blaze switched directions","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and moved toward his property .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"They loaded up what belongings they could ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"including three dogs and a 1930 model hot rod on a trailer .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"As he looked out his rear view mirror","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"he could see embers on the roof of his garage .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"He later gathered at the Arrowhead Bar and Grill in nearby Congress along with locals","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"and watched on TV","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"as he saw the fire destroy his house .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"Two hundred firefighters were working on the fire Sunday ,","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"and several hundred more were expected to arrive Monday .","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"The fire has forced the closure of parts of state Route 89 .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"Fire crews had no containment late Sunday .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"The Red Cross has opened two shelters in the area","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"- at Yavapai College in Prescott and at the Wickenburg High School gym .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":107,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":108,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":109,"text":"Billeaud reported from Phoenix .","depth":3},{"id":110,"text":"Associated Press writer Brian Skoloff in Yarnell , Arizona , and Associated Press reporter Martin Di Caro in Washington , D.C. , also contributed to this story .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":221,"left":214,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"l